title: Noel Coward Mysteries
description:
5 x 45 Minutes

As well as being a playwright, director, actor, composer, singer, actor and raconteur, a less well known side of Noel Coward - or so author Marcy Kahan would have us believe - was his role as a private detective and wartime spy. These 5 stories, featuring Malcolm Sinclair doing a wonderful impression of "the Master", have their tongue very firmly in their cheek and are tremendous fun.

The stories are:

1) Design For Murder

2) Blithe Spy

3) A Bullet At Balmain's

4) Death At The Desert Inn

5) Our Man In Jamaica.

Enjoy!
